            "description": "This anaglyph from NASA Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter spacecraft, shows Olympus Mons, the largest volcano in the Solar System. Constructed of lava flows, many aspects of this titanic volcano remain puzzling. 3D glasses are necessary to view this image.",
            "description_508": "This anaglyph from NASA Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter spacecraft, shows Olympus Mons, the largest volcano in the Solar System. Constructed of lava flows, many aspects of this titanic volcano remain puzzling. 3D glasses are necessary to view this image.",
            "keywords": [
              "Mars",
              "Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter MRO"
            ],
            "media_type": "image",
            "nasa_id": "PIA09569",
            "secondary_creator": "NASA/JPL/Univ. of Arizona",
            "title": "Anaglyph of the Basal Scarp of Olympus Mons Volcano"
          }
        ],
