            "date_created": "2015-02-09T00:00:00Z",
            "description": "Construction workers at Sauer in Oak Hill, Florida, work on the buildup of the first of 10 new work platforms that will be delivered for installation in high bay 3 of the Vehicle Assembly Building at NASA\u0027s Kennedy Space Center in Florida. A contract to modify high bay 3 was awarded by NASA to the Hensel Phelps Construction Co. of Orlando, Florida in March 2014. Sauer is a subcontractor to Hensel Phelps. The Ground Systems Development and Operations Program is overseeing upgrades and modifications to the high bay to support processing of NASA\u0027s Space Launch System and Orion spacecraft, and other exploration vehicles. Photo credit: NASA/Ben Smegelsky",
