        "data": [
          {
            "center": "KSC",
            "date_created": "2013-04-26T00:00:00Z",
            "description": "CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. -- At the Kennedy Space Center Visitor Complex in Florida, construction crews are removing 16,000 square feet of plastic shrink-wrap from the space shuttle Atlantis. The spacecraft was enclosed in the plastic shrink-wrap since November of last year to protect the artifact from dust and debris during construction of the 90,000-square-foot facility.      Last November, the space shuttle Atlantis made its historic final journey to its new home, traveling 10 miles from the Kennedy Space Center\u0027s Vehicle Assembly Building to the spaceport\u0027s visitor complex. The new $100 million \"Space Shuttle Atlantis\" facility will include interactive exhibits that tell the story of the 30-year Space Shuttle Program and highlights the future of space exploration. The \"Space Shuttle Atlantis\" exhibit scheduled to open June 29, 2013.Photo credit: NASA/Cory Huston",
